OL,3,CLocal pubs 'struggling to stay afloat'
OL,4,Cafter bus stop cut, says MS
OL,6,FThe MS said data for people alighting
OL,7,Fin Penrhynside was far more crucial
OL,8,Fand this should have determined the
OL,9,Ffinal decision.JShe wrote back to
OL,10,FArriva CEO Mike Cooper accusing the
OL,11,Fcompany of a "major oversight". Ms
OL,12,FFinch-Saunders said more people used
OL,13,Fbuses to reach the village than leave
OL,14,Fit as people struggle to walk up the
OL,15,Fsteep hill on which Penrhynside is
OL,16,Flocated.JShe added: "The data used by
OL,17,FArriva is flawed. It seems to only
OL,18,Fcount how many people get on, not off
OL,19,Fthe bus in Penrhynside. It is
OL,20,Fcompletely unreasonable to expect
OL,21,Fparents with prams, wheelchair users,
OL,22,Fthe elderly, and individuals on their
OL,23,Fown to take such an unsuitable route.
OL,24,F"With 34% of residents over 65 in
OL,25,FPenrhyn ward, it is apparent that the
OL,26,Flack of services is hitting the oldest
